# HTML

Chapter 1

```html
<h2>Write the date</h2>
<p>Write your wish</p>
```

- Elements
    
    consists of an opening tag, contents and a closing tag
    
    e.g. <p>Hello World!</p>
    
    `<p>`¬† **= paragraph element** 
    
    `<body>`¬†**= body element**
    
- Indentation
    
    (2 spaces for indent = 1 tab)
    
    **indentation isn‚Äôt required** however its good practice c:
    
    e.g.
    
    ```html
    <body>
      <p>üëã I'm a new web developer!</p> <!-- indent here -->
    </body>
    ```
    
    - coding question
        
        ```html
        <!-- Write code below üíñ -->
        <body>
          <p> Fire </p>
          <p> Water </p>
          <p> Earth </p>
          <p> Air </p>
        </body>
        
        ```
        
    
- Headings
    
    example
    
    ```html
    <body>
      <h1>Breaking News üö®</h1>
      <p>Florida man once evaded arrest by cartwheeling now running for mayor.</p>
    </body>
    ```
    
    There are six levels of headings:
    
    ```html
    <h1>Heading level 1</h1> <!-- 1 being the biggest -->
    <h2>Heading level 2</h2>
    <h3>Heading level 3</h3>
    <h4>Heading level 4</h4>
    <h5>Heading level 5</h5>
    <h6>Heading level 6</h6> <!-- 6 being the smallest -->
    ```
    
- Line Break
    
    instead of creating a seperate <p> tag to start a new line.. you can use the tag <br> to break the line and start it on a new line
    
    <br> is also a self closing tag , therefore it doesn‚Äôt need a closing tag to close
    
    example:
    
    ```html
    <body>
      <h1>Breaking News</h1>
      <p>Florida man robs convenience store with an alligator.<br>Leaves a baby Crocs behind.</p>
    </body>
    
    <!-- output --> 
    <!-- Breaking News --> 
    <!-- Florida man robs convenience store with an alligator. --> 
    <!-- Leaves a baby Crocs behind. --> 
    
    ```
    
    - example code using h1, h2 and line break
        
        ```html
        <!-- Write code below üíñ -->
        <!-- Write code below üíñ -->
        <body>
          <h1> Venezuelan Inflation Falls </h1>
          <h2> Jan 1 2005 </h2>
          <p>Inflation dropped to 19.2 percent this year, from 27.1 percent in 2003 <br> Consumer prices rose 1.6 percent in December after an increase of 1.7 percent in November. </p>
        </body>
        ```
        
- Text formatting
    - **`<b>`¬†element to¬†bold¬†text.**
    - **`<i>`¬†element to¬†*italicize*¬†text.**
    - **`<u>`¬†element to¬†underline¬†text.**
    - **`<s>`¬†element to¬†~~strikethrough~~¬†text.**
    
    example code
    
    ```html
    <p>This is the reminder that the <i>final exam</i> is <b>mandatory</b>.<br>
    It will be held on <u>Monday, October 14th</u> at <s>7PM</s> 8PM EST.</p>
    ```
    
    - coding question using them all
        
        ```html
        **<!-- Write code below üíñ -->
        <body>
        <p> <b>Cutting Down, Ramping Up:</b> We have a robust <br> 
        strategy for <s> low hanging fruits </s> mission-critical <br>
        objectives that move the needle at all costs. It's <br>
        time to double down on <b> revenue growth </b> while <br>
        <u> cutting costs</u>. This is a win-win initiative, a win for <br>
        us and our amazing shareholders!<br>
        
        P.S. After several strong sales months, we are <br>
        printing <b> Employee Appreciation Tees </b>! Will go on <br>
        sale Monday.
        </body>**
        
        ```
        
- Lists
    
    organizes 
    
    2 types of html lists:
    
    - **`<ul>`¬†Unordered lists**
    - how to
        
        ```html
        <ul> 
          <li>üß∫ Go to laundromat.</li>
          <li>üñ• Code for 45 min.</li>
          <li>üíÖ Take a bubble bath.</li>
        </ul>
        ```
        
    - **`<ol>`¬†Ordered lists (numbered list)**
    - how to
        
        ```html
        <ol>
          <li>üß∫ Go to laundromat.</li>
          <li>üñ• Code for 45 min.</li>
          <li>üíÖ Take a bubble bath.</li>
        </ol>
        ```
        
    - coding question using them both
        
        ```html
        <!-- Write code below üíñ -->
        <body>
        <h1> Ingredients </h1>
        <ul>
          <li>milk</li>
          <li>eggs</li>
          <li>cake mix</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2> Instructions </h2>
        <ol>
          <li>first add milk to a bowl</li>
          <li>then add 2 eggs and mix thoroughly</li>
          <li>add in cake mix gradually</li>
        </ol>
        </body>
        ```
        
- Links
    
    How users connect to other sites and browse the web
    
    to add a link, html uses ¬†****`<a>`¬†**an anchor element!** 
    
    **This link tag allows us to add a¬†[hyperlink](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hyperlink)¬†to a piece of text.**
    
    further explanation of difference between a and href:
    
    | HTML Part | What it Does |
    | --- | --- |
    | `<a>` | Says: ‚ÄúHey browser, I‚Äôm making a link here.‚Äù |
    | `href="..."` | Says: ‚ÄúThis is where the link should go when clicked.‚Äù |
    | Link text (between `<a>` and `</a>`) | This is what the user sees and clicks. |
    
    **`src`¬†= for ‚Äúsource‚Äù**
    
    - examples:
        
        href when linking.. - websites, email, sms, phone number
        
        src when linking.. - images
        
        ```html
        <a href="https://archive.org/web">Internet Archive</a> 
        <!-- links to website -->
        <!-- the use of "href" adds the link to the text -->
        ```
        
        ```html
        <a href="mailto:frankie@gmail.com">üìß</a>
        <a href="tel:212-555-2368">ü§ô</a>
        <a href="sms:320-250-HTML">üí¨</a>
        
        <!-- links to email, phone and messages -->
        ```
        
        ```html
        <p>Here's a cute pic:</p>
        <img src="https://i.redd.it/5unn16axx1v81.jpg">
        
        <!-- instead of 'a' it's 'img' -->
        <!-- links to an image -->
        ```
        
    - coding question
        
        ```html
        <!-- Write code below üíñ -->
        <body>
        <h1> Missing Pet Alert! <br> Pet Name: Aurora </h1>
        <img src= "https://www.munchkincatguide.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/munchkincatslider2.jpg">This is how she looks</img>
        <p> She is light brown, has short paws and is very fluffy! </p>
        <p> Contact Information: </p>
        <a href= "tel:8367876">call us now if you find her!</a>
        <a href= "mailto:missingaurora@yahoo.com">or email us!</a>
        </body>
        ```
        
- coding question: creating website for band
    
    ```html
    <!-- Write code below üíñ -->
    <body>
      <h1> <b> Suicideboys </b> </h1>
        <h3>Artists Names: Ruby da Cherry and Scrim</h3>
          <img src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/b4/fa/d2/b4fad27e2d3ce99992609d1b2c7f0a7c.jpg"></img>
    <p> <s>Blurb:</s> <br> American hip hop duo</p>
    <a href="https://suicideboystore.com/?srsltid=AfmBOorG1w2NCgcSwWBenSxVL7HZc8C9SUorbNO6NeqgtMiKczlHL7KF">MERCH</a>
    <ul> 
